  <static seed="1161" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/simplifyRationalExpressions81.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{5ry-r^{2}y^{2}}{r^{2}y^{2}-2ry-15}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{ry}{ry+3}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common terms:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{5ry-r^{2}y^{2}}{r^{2}y^{2}-2ry-15}} \amp = \frac{{ry\mathopen{}\left(5-ry\right)}}{{\left(ry-5\right)\mathopen{}\left(ry+3\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{-ry\mathopen{}\left(ry-5\right)}}{{\left(ry-5\right)\mathopen{}\left(ry+3\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{ry}{ry+3}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
